  <section class="py-16 bg-tjb-cream">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-center" style="font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;">Your Questions About Birth Plans, Answered</h2>
      <p class="text-tjb-gray mb-8 text-center">The things first-time moms ask us most, answered honestly.</p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="border border-tjb-lavender-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white group">
          <summary class="text-base font-semibold text-tjb-charcoal cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            <span>What is a birth plan, and do I really need one?</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-tjb-lavender-500 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0 ml-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">A birth plan is a document that spells out your preferences for labor, delivery, and postpartum care. It's not a rigid checklist — it's a communication tool that helps your medical team know what matters to you. The <a href="/birth-plan-template/" class="text-tjb-lavender-600 hover:underline">free Joyful Birth Plan</a> covers every stage and works in your real hospital room.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="border border-tjb-lavender-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white group">
          <summary class="text-base font-semibold text-tjb-charcoal cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            <span>Can I fill out a birth plan on my phone?</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-tjb-lavender-500 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0 ml-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">Yes! The <a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/true-joy-birthing/id6760793180" class="text-tjb-lavender-600 hover:underline">True Joy Birthing app</a> lets you build your birth plan step by step on your phone. Nine guided sections walk you through hospital preferences, pain management, and more — and you can update it anytime. Prefer the fillable PDF? <a href="/birth-plan-template/" class="text-tjb-lavender-600 hover:underline">Download it free here</a>.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="border border-tjb-lavender-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white group">
          <summary class="text-base font-semibold text-tjb-charcoal cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            <span>What if my doctor recommends something I didn't expect?</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-tjb-lavender-500 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0 ml-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">That's exactly what a birth plan is for. It gives you the words when your doctor recommends something you hadn't thought about. The <a href="/guided-birth-plan-walkthrough/" class="text-tjb-lavender-600 hover:underline">Guided Birth Plan Walkthrough</a> course covers what to say in these moments, and the <a href="/birth-plan-confidence-session/#book" class="text-tjb-lavender-600 hover:underline">1:1 Confidence Session</a> lets you practice the conversation.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="border border-tjb-lavender-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white group">
          <summary class="text-base font-semibold text-tjb-charcoal cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            <span>How do I choose between the PDF and the app?</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-tjb-lavender-500 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0 ml-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">Both are free! The <strong>app</strong> is best if you want step-by-step guidance, the ability to update your plan anytime, and share it with your care team. The <strong>PDF</strong> is best if you want a printable one-pager your nurse can read in two minutes. Many families use both — build in the app, print the PDF for the hospital bag.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="border border-tjb-lavender-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white group">
          <summary class="text-base font-semibold text-tjb-charcoal cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            <span>Is there a doula or midwife directory?</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-tjb-lavender-500 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0 ml-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-tjb-gray mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed">Yes — use the <a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/true-joy-birthing/id6760793180" class="text-tjb-lavender-600 hover:underline">True Joy Birthing app</a> to find doulas and midwives in your area. You can also browse our <a href="/birth-support/" class="text-tjb-lavender-600 hover:underline">city-by-city guides</a> for local hospital info, doula costs, and Medicaid status.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .fade-up {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(12px);
      transition: opacity 0.6s ease-out, transform 0.6s ease-out;
    }
    .fade-up.is-visible {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      .fade-up {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: none;
        transition: none;
      }
    }
  </style>
  <script>
    // Fade-in reveals on scroll
    const fadeEls = document.querySelectorAll('.fade-up');
    if (fadeEls.length && 'IntersectionObserver' in window) {
      const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
        entries.forEach(entry => {
          if (entry.isIntersecting) {
            entry.target.classList.add('is-visible');
            observer.unobserve(entry.target);
          }
        });
      }, { threshold: 0.15 });
      fadeEls.forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
    } else {
      // Fallback: show everything immediately
      fadeEls.forEach(el => el.classList.add('is-visible'));
    }
  </script>


